:—Flowering and fruiting from April to June.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C340652FE215111D9BFBFF53FDF2FEF7" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE536A4E215111D9BFBFF53FDF2FEF7" blockId="3.[136,1452,158,616]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis id="B92EEAB6E215111D9BFBFF53FE9DFF2B" bold="true" box="[189,318,194,220]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Etymology</emphasis>
:—The specific epithet ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D27E215111D990BFF53FCA5FF2B" box="[589,774,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cirsium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hupingshanicum">
<emphasis id="B92EEAB6E215111D990BFF53FCA5FF2B" box="[589,774,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">hupingshanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ is derived from the 
<typeStatus id="54E18806E215111D98AAFF52FBBFFF2A" box="[1004,1052,195,221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">type</typeStatus>
locality, the Hupingshan Mountain, Shimen County, 
<collectingRegion id="499EF846E215111D9A05FF76FE58FEF7" box="[323,507,230,257]" country="China" name="Hunan" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Hunan Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F34D7634E215111D9940FF77FDEEFEF7" box="[518,589,230,256]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C340652FE215111D9BFBFE9BFE18FE2E" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BE536A4E215111D9BFBFE9BFE18FE2E" blockId="3.[136,1452,158,616]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis id="B92EEAB6E215111D9BFBFE9BFE40FED3" bold="true" box="[189,483,266,292]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D27E215111D9940FE9AFC81FED3" box="[518,802,266,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cirsium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hupingshanicum">
<emphasis id="B92EEAB6E215111D9940FE9AFC81FED3" box="[518,802,266,293]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Cirsium hupingshanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently only known from two localities (
<figureCitation id="13612A21E215111D9E61FE9BFAC8FED3" box="[1319,1387,266,292]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,726,1707]" captionTargetId="figure-186@3.[151,1436,713,1717]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distribution map of Cirsium hupingshanicum (red circle)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501478/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), one is its 
<typeStatus id="54E18806E215111D9B85FEBEFF50FEBE" box="[195,243,303,329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">type</typeStatus>
locality: Shimen county, 
<collectingRegion id="499EF846E215111D9957FEBEFD6BFEBF" box="[529,712,302,329]" country="China" name="Hunan" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Hunan province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F34D7634E215111D9995FEBFFCB9FEBF" box="[723,794,302,328]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">China</collectingCountry>
. On the website of Chinese Field Herbarium (https://www. cfh.ac.cn/album/ShowPhoto.aspx?photoid=55ab405d-bbb9-430b-952e-1fb4e3990e2e), we also found a similar plant from Hefeng county, 
<collectingRegion id="499EF846E215111D9A30FEE7FD84FE67" box="[374,551,374,400]" country="China" name="Hubei" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Hubei Province</collectingRegion>
. These two localities are very close to each other. It is reasonable to infer that the population of Hefeng is most likely to belong to the same species as Hupingshan specimen. It occurs on the roadside at altitudes of about 
<specimenCount id="9D5CFD2DE215111D9A2BFE2FFE18FE2E" box="[365,443,446,473]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" type="generic">
<quantity id="4CA29B41E215111D9A2BFE2FFE14FE2E" box="[365,439,446,473]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" unit="m" value="350.0">350 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C340652FE215111D9BFBFE73FF5DFD9F" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE536A4E215111D9BFBFE73FF5DFD9F" blockId="3.[136,1452,158,616]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis id="B92EEAB6E215111D9BFBFE73FE98FE0B" bold="true" box="[189,315,482,508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Discussion</emphasis>
:—Because its phyllaries lack marginal spinules, wings, and scarious appendage and leaves abaxially lack spinules, the new species should belong to 
<emphasis id="B92EEAB6E215111D99F0FD96FD73FDD6" box="[694,720,519,545]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">C.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D27E215111D9850FD96FCD3FDD6" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1754" box="[790,880,519,545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cirsium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92EEAB6E215111D9850FD96FCD3FDD6" box="[790,880,519,545]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Cirsium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D27E215111D98C7FD96FB3DFDD7" box="[897,1182,518,545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cirsium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hupingshanicum">
<emphasis id="B92EEAB6E215111D98C7FD96FB3DFDD7" box="[897,1182,518,545]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Cirsium hupingshanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mostly similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D27E215111D9ED4FD96FF5DFDB3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cirsium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="japonicum">
<emphasis id="B92EEAB6E215111D9ED4FD96FF5DFDB3" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">C. japonicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B92EEAB6E215111D9A71FDBAFE4CFDB3" box="[311,495,554,581]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D27E215111D9A71FDBAFE48FDB3" box="[311,491,554,581]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cirsium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="racemiforme">C. racemiforme</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The comparison of morphological characters between these three species are shown in 
<tableCitation id="C6D8031FE215111D9BE2FDDFFF5BFD9F" box="[164,248,590,616]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,224,160,184]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison of morphological characters of Cirsium hupingshanicum, C. japonicum and C. racemiforme." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF25662CE212111A9BCEFF31FAC5FF40" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" tableUuid="DF25662CE212111A9BCEFF31FAC5FF40">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
